[Gastro-intestinal outbreaks are inevitable following severe flooding,
because the drinking water supply becomes contaminated by sewage.
Commonest causes of diarrhea are cholera, _Salmonella typhi_ (typhoid) &
_S.paratyphi_ (paratyphoid), and of dysentery, _Shigella_. - Mod.JW
